<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="470" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1876,2009]" pageId="7" pageNumber="470">
Three males and one female were captured in PNSD, one male in 2011 and the remainder in 2014. Specimens of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="470" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leucophrys">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="470">M. leucophrys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were observed on the hilltop flying slowly about one to two meters from the ground during the end of the day (around 17:00h.).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="471" pageId="7" pageNumber="470" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1876,2009]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="471" pageId="7" pageNumber="470">
<taxonomicName box="[199,417,1984,2009]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="470" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leucophrys">
<emphasis box="[199,417,1984,2009]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="470">Mesene leucophrys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the species with the most extensive synonymic list of the genus (
<bibRefCitation author="Callaghan" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="471" pageId="7" pageNumber="470" refString="Callaghan, C. J. &amp; Lamas, G. (2004) Riodinidae. In: Lamas, G. (Ed.), Checklist: Part 4 A. Hesperioidea-Papilionoidea. In: Heppner, J. B. (Ed.), Atlas of Neotropical Lepidoptera 5 A. Association for Tropical Lepidoptera / Scientific Publishers, Gainesville, pp. 141 - 170." type="book chapter" year="2004">Callaghan &amp; Lamas 2004</bibRefCitation>
), with nine synonyms, which serves as an indication of its variable phenotype. The specimens from 
<collectionCode box="[151,223,188,212]" pageId="8" pageNumber="471">PNSD</collectionCode>
have a phenotype similar to that of the 
<typeStatus box="[681,729,189,213]" pageId="8" pageNumber="471">type</typeStatus>
specimen of 
<taxonomicName box="[884,1047,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="471" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leucophrys">
<emphasis box="[884,1047,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="471">M. leucophrys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Warren et al. 2016" authorityName="Warren et al." authorityYear="2016" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="471" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paraena">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="471">M. paraena</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Warren" box="[258,471,223,248]" pageId="8" pageNumber="471" refString="Warren, A. D., Davis, K. J., Stangeland, E. M., Pelham, J. P. &amp; Grishin, N. V. (2016) Illustrated lists of American butterflies (North and South America). Available from: http: // butterfliesofamerica. com / L / Neotropical. htm (accessed 23 May 2016)" type="journal article" year="2016">
Warren 
<emphasis box="[348,404,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="471">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Due to distribution of 
<collectionCode box="[735,789,224,248]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15690" name="California Academy of Sciences" pageId="8" pageNumber="471">CAS</collectionCode>
and morphology of male genitalia, this species belongs to the “ 
<taxonomicName box="[204,293,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="471" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phareus">
<emphasis box="[204,293,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="471">phareus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” species group.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
